<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="206">3.1.2. <em>Alternative 2:</em> Saving basic settings in the Setup menu</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>Setup » Markets » bol.com » Settings</strong> menu, you can carry out the basic settings for bol.com. However, note that bol.com delivery times cannot be mapped in this menu. Go through the bol.com assistant to map delivery times with plentymarkets.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting up bol.com in the Setup menu:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Markets » bol.com » Settings</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings. Pay attention to the explanations given in <a href="#basic-settings-bol">Table 2</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.<br>
→ The settings are saved.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Assistants » Omni-Channel</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the assistant <strong>Base settings - bol.com</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Navigate to the step <strong>Delivery times</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Link one or more bol.com delivery times with delivery times saved in plentymarkets.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Complete the assistant.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
